Amazing customer service! I work at the Willis Tower and yesterday I lost my credit card on my way to Chipotle (less than a block away). Of course I didn't notice until I had already ordered and went to pull out my card. They insisted that I take the food "on the house". They were so friendly, kind, and understanding about it that I didn't even know what to say. I promised to come back today to pay for it, and they insisted that I NOT come back to pay and that it was really on the house. I'm heading there right now to pay for my lunch from yesterday anyway, but their understanding and generosity really meant a lot in a very awkward situation. Thanks Chipotle!!

This Chipotle is terrible!! The employees are loud, obnoxious, and seem to absolutely hate customers! Has Chipotle not had enough issues with sickening the public due to its problems with cleanliness? Now that they are closing all the stores for a half-day, the employees are coming back angry with customers for complaining, I guess. Well, if the goal of Chipotle is to eliminate customers, the store at 311 S. Wacker is certainly doing its job! Further, the manager named Eva or Eve is clearly a big part of the problem. She can often be seen sitting at a table with multiple staff members as they are talking and laughing loudly. This is made worse by the fact that as she parties with the staff at a table, customers are waiting to be served at the counter! It is really a disgrace. She is also extremely rude. I wish upper management, if it is not too busy counting its money from the heydays of Chipotle, will stop and realize that one store and one manager can do a lot of damage to a brand. The store at 311 South Wacker managed by Eve or Eva seems determined to pile on the damage to what was once a strong brand. Now Chipotle is really just another restaurant that had its time in the sun and could not last since the customers, which made Chipotle was it was, are not hated by employees such as Eve or Eva at 311 South Wacker, Chicago.
